        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 18 at 5:25PM CDT until August 18 at 6:30PM CDT by NWS Quad Cities IA IL</headline>
        <description>SVRDVN

The National Weather Service in the Quad Cities has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Eastern Rock Island County in northwestern Illinois...
Southern Whiteside County in northwestern Illinois...
Northern Henry County in northwestern Illinois...

* Until 630 PM CDT.

* At 524 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Port Byron to near Sherrard, moving east at 30
mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Moline, Rock Island, East Moline, Sterling, Morrison, Silvis,
Geneseo, Colona, Milan, Camanche, Coal Valley, Prophetstown,
Hampton, Orion, Port Byron, Erie, Atkinson, Rapids City, Albany,
and Cordova.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 80 in Illinois between mile markers 1 and 28.
Interstate 74 in Illinois between mile markers 1 and 20.
Interstate 88 between mile markers 1 and 38.
Interstate 280 between mile markers 15 and 18.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
sturdy building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with these storms, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
